title Algorithm-Agnostic Architecture — How Existing Components Support Sorting Strategies

' Added \n for title padding
package "Existing Architecture\n" #FAFAFA {

    class CardManager <<Base>> #LightBlue {
        -- **Card Logic (705 lines)** --
        + values: Array
        + sorted_all: Array
        + cards_array: Array[Card]
        + slots: Array[CardBuffer]
        + move_count: int
        --
        + generate_random_values()
        + generate_completed_card_array()
        + fill_card_container()
        + create_buffer_slots()
        + check_sorting_order(): bool
        + check_player_buffer_contiguity(): bool
        --
        <i>Reused by all modes</i>
    }

    class CardBuffer <<UI Component>> #Wheat {
        + occupied_by: Card
        + slot_index: int
        --
        + place_card(card: Card)
        + remove_card(): Card
        + is_empty(): bool
    }

    class MultiplayerCardManager <<Multiplayer>> #LightGreen {
        -- **Sync Protocol (1143 lines)** --
        + is_host: bool
        + my_client_id: int
        + game_state_synced: bool
        --
        + setup_multiplayer_sync()
        + broadcast_initial_game_state()
        + sync_card_moved()
        + sync_card_entered_buffer()
        + sync_card_left_buffer()
        --
        <i>extends card_manager.gd</i>
    }

    class BarrierManager <<RefCounted>> #LightYellow {
        -- **3-State FSM (113 lines)** --
        + current_state: BarrierState
        + threads_at_barrier: Dictionary
        + main_thread_id: int
        --
        + enter_waiting_state()
        + activate_barrier()
        + release_barrier()
        + determine_main_thread()
        --
        «enum» BarrierState
        {RUNNING, WAITING_AT_BARRIER,
         BARRIER_ACTIVE}
    }
}

' Added \n for title padding
package "Supported Strategies (no code changes)\n" #FFFFF0 {

    note as MergeSortNote #PaleGreen
      **Parallel Merge Sort Strategy**
      ────────────────────────────
      Players use existing mechanics:
      • Divide cards among players (informal agreement)
      • Each player sorts locally using private buffers
      • Barrier synchronization between merge rounds
      • Main thread merges adjacent sorted runs
      ────────────────────────────
      **Uses:** Buffers (heavy), Barriers (heavy)
      **Teaches:** Data decomposition, reduction
    end note

    note as QuicksortNote #MistyRose
      **Parallel Quicksort Strategy**
      ────────────────────────────
      Players use existing mechanics:
      • Agree on a pivot card
      • Collaboratively partition in shared container
      • Split into sub-groups for recursive sorting
      • Repeat until all sub-arrays sorted
      ────────────────────────────
      **Uses:** Shared container (heavy), Barriers (light)
      **Teaches:** Load imbalance, task parallelism
    end note
}

' --- RELATIONSHIPS ---

' Inheritance straight down
CardManager <|-- MultiplayerCardManager : extends\n(path-based)

' Force composition strictly to the right to keep the diagram narrow
CardManager "1" *-right- "0..*" CardBuffer : slots
MultiplayerCardManager "1" *-right- "1" BarrierManager : barrier_manager

' Strategy support arrows flowing downwards
MultiplayerCardManager ..> MergeSortNote : supports via\nbuffers +\nbarriers
MultiplayerCardManager ..> QuicksortNote : supports via\nshared\ncontainer
BarrierManager ..> MergeSortNote : merge-round\nsynchronization
CardBuffer ..> MergeSortNote : local sorting\nphase
CardBuffer ..> QuicksortNote : optional staging\nduring partition

center footer Existing architecture supports any parallel sorting strategy without modifications

@enduml